    {
        "sha": "c97adb5d53252a65a12a1a547c2bac3146b86488",
        "author": "Ege Balcı",
        "email": "17179401+EgeBalci@users.noreply.github.com",
        "date": "2026-05-01T22:18:42Z",
        "message": "Merge pull request #28 from Drewsif/master\n\nFix various encoding/obfuscation bugs and improve payload reliability",
        "url": "https://github.com/EgeBalci/sgn/commit/c97adb5d53252a65a12a1a547c2bac3146b86488"
    },
    {
        "sha": "ecc578b28c0bd889103f435683fb0b5b4bd6f39f",
        "author": "Drew Bonasera",
        "email": "drewbonasera@google.com",
        "date": "2026-04-29T08:12:25Z",
        "message": "Apply encoder options within the main loop and fix various bugs related to encoding, obfuscation, and file handling.\r\n\r\n- feat(cli): Apply obfuscation, encoding, and safe options in main loop\r\n- feat(obfuscation): Allow disabling garbage instruction generation via obfuscation limit\r\n- fix(encoder): Correct schema size calculation for x64 architecture\r\n- fix(encoder): Pad encoded payload with NOPs to ensure schema alignment\r\n- fix(obfuscation): Add fallback for random register selection in garbage generation\r\n- fix(cli): Truncate output file on write and ensure it is closed\r\n- fix(examples): Correct casing in sgn package import path\r\n- style(encoder): Remove trailing whitespace from register save definitions",
        "url": "https://github.com/EgeBalci/sgn/commit/ecc578b28c0bd889103f435683fb0b5b4bd6f39f"
    },
    {
        "sha": "e2ccc66ff3fb26358bc3a2e378d1c8d22bcf10d0",
        "author": "Drew Bonasera",
        "email": "drewbonasera@google.com",
        "date": "2026-04-29T07:35:35Z",
        "message": "Corrects payload selection logic and several register definitions and selection mechanisms.\r\nThis commit also optimizes bad-byte checking and improves code style.\r\n\r\n- fix(main): Correct payload selection logic for ASCII and bad byte constraints\r\n- refactor(main): Improve readability of payload selection conditions\r\n- fix(sgn): Correct register definitions for ESI, EDI, and RDI\r\n- fix(sgn): Remove PUSH/POP of RSP from x64 register save/restore opcodes\r\n- fix(sgn): Rework random register selection to prevent returning invalid registers\r\n- perf(utils): Optimize `ContainsBytes` by using `bytes.IndexByte`\r\n- style(utils): Export `ContainsBytes` function\r\n- chore(main): Remove unused `bytes` import",
        "url": "https://github.com/EgeBalci/sgn/commit/e2ccc66ff3fb26358bc3a2e378d1c8d22bcf10d0"
    },
    {
        "sha": "6203484fcdb41fc61c0c92c2a82c8a73835f1161",
        "author": "Drew Bonasera",
        "email": "drewbonasera@google.com",
        "date": "2026-04-29T06:45:39Z",
        "message": "Fixes several bugs in encoding and obfuscation and adds a new payload execution stress test.\r\n\r\n- fix(encode): Remove redundant modulo operations from ADD/SUB ciphers\r\n- fix(obfuscate): Remove \"JMP 2\" from the list of safe garbage instructions\r\n- fix(obfuscate): Use correct slice length when selecting random garbage instruction\r\n- fix(sgn): Correct register exclusion logic in GetSafeRandomRegister\r\n- test: Add integration stress test for payload execution on Windows",
        "url": "https://github.com/EgeBalci/sgn/commit/6203484fcdb41fc61c0c92c2a82c8a73835f1161"
    },
